24:45.092 --> 24:46.441
That's not crazy.

24:46.485 --> 24:49.488
And we kept getting
together and breaking up.

24:49.531 --> 24:50.750
That's not crazy.

24:50.793 --> 24:52.795
And then I started
working two jobs

24:52.839 --> 24:55.537
so I could buy him a car,

24:55.581 --> 24:57.234
which he totaled.

24:57.278 --> 24:58.888
DUI.

24:58.932 --> 25:03.806
And then we got married
while he was in prison...

25:03.850 --> 25:06.766
And while I was
fucking my therapist...

25:06.809 --> 25:08.289
And his son.

25:08.332 --> 25:09.682
Okay, that counts.

25:12.685 --> 25:14.077
So, what are your hobbies?

25:14.121 --> 25:15.992
Besides crippling anxiety?

25:16.036 --> 25:18.517
I mean, what do you like to do?

25:18.560 --> 25:21.998
A big part of recovery is
finding something to live for.

25:22.042 --> 25:27.177
You ought to try things.
Read, learn... Play.

25:27.221 --> 25:28.962
Get curious.

27:37.830 --> 27:40.093
Excuse me.

27:41.747 --> 27:44.663
Excuse me. Excuse me!

27:44.706 --> 27:47.927
Hi. You can't play those.

27:47.970 --> 27:49.493
I'm sorry, who are you?

27:49.537 --> 27:50.886
I live here. You
can't play those.

27:50.930 --> 27:52.845
Oh, Maddie didn't
tell me you live here.

27:52.888 --> 27:54.281
Maddie's my sister.

27:54.324 --> 27:56.675
Oh, hi. I'm Joy.
Nice to meet you.

27:56.718 --> 27:58.024
Okay, great.

27:58.067 --> 28:00.548
Now, please get
out of my garage.

28:02.724 --> 28:05.248
I need
you to leave now.

28:08.948 --> 28:11.124
My name is Jim.

29:19.409 --> 29:21.281
Fucking shit. Fuck.

30:00.407 --> 30:01.408
Hi.

30:15.248 --> 30:17.076
Right hand on the high hat.

30:17.119 --> 30:19.818
One, two, three, four.

30:29.523 --> 30:32.265
Don't squeeze them
with a death grip.

30:32.308 --> 30:34.136
Hold them like baby birds.

30:34.180 --> 30:35.790
Let them breathe.

30:36.878 --> 30:38.445
Good.

30:38.488 --> 30:41.404
Okay, now same beat,
please, and no showboating.

31:20.966 --> 31:22.228
What are you doing?

31:23.142 --> 31:24.926
I said no showboating.

31:24.970 --> 31:27.015
-I was backing you up.
-No, no.

31:27.059 --> 31:28.364
You know what? You got to go.

31:29.931 --> 31:30.714
Go.

31:41.900 --> 31:46.382
I think every woman I
date is the woman of my dreams.

31:46.426 --> 31:48.732
If a woman is even nice to me,

31:48.776 --> 31:51.822
I've already pictured
her in a wedding dress,

31:51.866 --> 31:54.564
and when she does make
herself available,

31:54.608 --> 31:57.002
I just want to go
find someone else.

31:57.045 --> 31:59.134
Another fantasy.

31:59.178 --> 32:02.181
Thanks for
everyone's shares.

32:02.224 --> 32:05.358
I really related to all of them,

32:06.011 --> 32:07.708
so thank you.

32:08.752 --> 32:09.623
Um...

32:12.408 --> 32:14.410
My dad was obsessed with women.

32:18.066 --> 32:22.418
Our garage was...
Covered in centerfolds.

32:23.332 --> 32:25.421
Naked women everywhere.

32:26.857 --> 32:30.426
And he watched a lot of porn.

32:30.470 --> 32:35.475
Whenever I was home alone,
I'd sneak into the garage,

32:35.518 --> 32:37.564
and I watched it.

32:39.261 --> 32:41.046
I think I was, like, five or six

32:41.089 --> 32:42.438
when I started doing it.

32:45.398 --> 32:47.617
I remember, the first time
I watched it, I was like,

32:47.661 --> 32:50.794
"I don't know what
the hell this is!"

32:50.838 --> 32:54.450
But... My body felt crazy.

32:54.494 --> 32:56.975
I wanted to watch
it all the time.

33:00.804 --> 33:04.460
I looked at all those women...

33:06.071 --> 33:07.202
And I thought...

33:08.856 --> 33:11.206
"That's what I want to be.

33:11.250 --> 33:12.903
That's who my dad loves."

33:16.124 --> 33:17.604
I don't know, whatever.

33:18.953 --> 33:19.998
Thanks for letting me share.

33:24.219 --> 33:25.612
Hey, you didn't tell me

33:25.655 --> 33:27.396
your brother lives
with your grandma.

33:27.440 --> 33:28.658
He didn't bother you, did he?

33:29.442 --> 33:31.357
No.

33:31.400 --> 33:34.360
Well, he's got real
problems, mental health issues,

33:34.403 --> 33:37.711
and he's basically a recluse.

33:37.754 --> 33:39.800
I'm surprised he even
came out of the house.

33:39.843 --> 33:42.237
I saw him checking the mail,

33:42.281 --> 33:45.197
and I introduced
myself to be polite.

33:45.240 --> 33:46.241
No biggie at all.

33:46.285 --> 33:48.156
Good.

33:48.200 --> 33:50.376
Just leave him alone, and
he'll leave you alone, okay?

36:23.268 --> 36:25.008
That was tight.

36:25.052 --> 36:26.053
So good.

36:26.096 --> 36:27.272
Holy shit, that was tight.

36:27.315 --> 36:28.838
We got to record that next time.

36:28.882 --> 36:30.753
Yeah.

36:30.797 --> 36:32.799
My recording setup is pretty lo-fi,
you know, but it sounds good.

36:32.842 --> 36:34.496
I can add some reverb,
dip the treble.

36:34.540 --> 36:36.759
Yeah, yeah, verb the trebs.

36:39.849 --> 36:41.373
What's your grandma like?

36:41.416 --> 36:43.418
Nana? She's cool.

36:45.159 --> 36:47.988
She basically raised
me and Maddie.

36:48.031 --> 36:49.859
She takes care of me.
I take care of her.

36:49.903 --> 36:52.297
It's a symbiotic relationship.

36:52.340 --> 36:54.386
She likes watching musicals

36:54.429 --> 36:56.823
and enjoys the works
of Shakespeare.

36:59.042 --> 36:59.782
What else do you want to know?

37:03.830 --> 37:05.788
I'm hungry. You want to eat?

37:08.269 --> 37:11.229
Keep the change, my man.

37:11.272 --> 37:13.274
Come on, let's eat
at the table inside.

37:13.318 --> 37:15.102
Oh...

37:15.145 --> 37:18.279
I probably shouldn't
go in your house.

37:18.323 --> 37:20.629
I promised myself I'd only
go as far as this garage.

37:39.300 --> 37:42.042
You really like orange juice.

37:42.085 --> 37:43.696
I love orange juice.

37:51.791 --> 37:54.097
So you're in 12-step
with my sister?

37:54.141 --> 37:55.316
Mm-hmm.

37:55.360 --> 37:56.752
Is she your sponsor?

37:57.275 --> 37:58.450
Yeah.

37:59.451 --> 38:01.061
Do you like her?

38:01.104 --> 38:02.018
Yeah.

38:03.890 --> 38:05.457
-Do you?
-What?

38:05.500 --> 38:06.632
Do you like her?

38:06.675 --> 38:07.720
Yes.

38:12.638 --> 38:14.292
You're not hungry?

38:14.335 --> 38:18.600
It's been really hard to eat...
And sleep,

38:18.644 --> 38:21.516
and, like, be a human being.

38:21.560 --> 38:23.213
Everything's a fucking trigger.

38:24.780 --> 38:26.347
What does that mean?

38:26.391 --> 38:28.393
Trigger?

38:28.436 --> 38:34.355
Uh, something that intensely
makes you feel a feeling

38:34.399 --> 38:37.489
that you really
don't want to feel.

38:37.532 --> 38:41.057
It makes you react compulsively.

38:41.101 --> 38:43.146
Oh, I have a lot
of triggers then.

38:43.190 --> 38:44.496
Exactly.

38:44.539 --> 38:46.149
The whole fucking
world is a trigger.

38:46.193 --> 38:48.369
I know. I'm triggered
by everything.

38:48.413 --> 38:49.675
I'm triggered by pancakes.

38:49.718 --> 38:51.198
Pancakes?

38:51.241 --> 38:52.939
My boyfriend...

38:52.982 --> 38:56.159
Ex-boyfriend made good pancakes.

38:56.203 --> 38:58.771
I'm triggered by
family, sad songs...

39:00.381 --> 39:01.208
Pierogies.

39:02.252 --> 39:03.819
I could see that.

39:07.997 --> 39:10.739
What is happening right now?
What are you doing?

39:13.220 --> 39:16.745
Nana taught us to do
that when we were little.

39:16.789 --> 39:18.530
She said, "Cookies
don't create my fortune.

39:18.573 --> 39:21.010
"I create my fortune."

39:21.054 --> 39:22.577
And she taught us
that there are many

39:22.621 --> 39:24.362
much better tasting
cookies in the world,

39:24.405 --> 39:26.668
and we shouldn't waste our
dessert on a shit cookie.

39:28.278 --> 39:29.410
Nana's amazing.

39:29.454 --> 39:31.978
I know. She's cool.

39:32.021 --> 39:32.805
You're cool.

39:49.996 --> 39:51.693
I'm glad Maddie's
sponsoring again.

39:51.737 --> 39:52.868
I didn't think she would.

39:53.391 --> 39:55.218
Why?

39:55.262 --> 39:56.829
Well, she used to
sponsor this girl Kelly.

39:56.872 --> 39:58.396
She stayed here too.

39:58.439 --> 40:00.528
Oh, really? What happened?

40:00.572 --> 40:01.877
She killed herself.

40:05.925 --> 40:07.927
She was a
really nice person too.

40:10.451 --> 40:12.671
Nana's about to wake
up from her nap.

40:12.714 --> 40:14.934
Her naps are always
two hours long.

40:14.977 --> 40:16.805
Not a minute less,
not a minute more.

40:16.849 --> 40:18.154
How'd she do it?

40:18.894 --> 40:20.243
What?

40:20.287 --> 40:21.984
How'd she kill herself?

40:22.028 --> 40:24.726
Oh, she just took
a bunch of pills

40:24.770 --> 40:26.467
and passed out in the bathtub.

40:26.511 --> 40:28.034
Pretty standard stuff.

40:32.038 --> 40:33.909
Hi, Kelly.

40:34.519 --> 40:36.956
It's me, Joy.

40:39.524 --> 40:43.919
I don't want to be weird.
I just wanted to say hi...

40:48.271 --> 40:51.753
And I'm sorry, and...

40:54.147 --> 40:55.888
I get you.

40:58.543 --> 41:01.110
I'm gonna try harder for
the both of us, okay?

41:57.602 --> 41:59.517
How did it sound?

41:59.560 --> 42:00.387
I think we got it.

42:01.301 --> 42:03.042
I can do it faster.

42:05.392 --> 42:06.698
Do you want me to?

42:11.572 --> 42:13.182
Hey, can I ask you something?

42:14.923 --> 42:17.099
Why did Kelly kill herself?

42:17.143 --> 42:18.927
How can I answer that?

42:18.971 --> 42:22.540
I mean... Did you have any
sense of what was wrong?

42:22.583 --> 42:24.019
No.

42:24.063 --> 42:25.847
Did she give you
any warning signs?

42:25.891 --> 42:29.590
Maybe she knew she
was terminally ill.

42:29.634 --> 42:32.550
Maybe she was bored.
Maybe she got dumped

42:32.593 --> 42:33.812
and was sad like you.

42:41.428 --> 42:44.736
Well... Nana's still sleeping.

42:48.000 --> 42:50.089
What are you doing right now?

42:51.394 --> 42:53.179
I hope so.

42:53.222 --> 42:55.398
Bobby certainly has taken
charge of those boys.

42:55.442 --> 42:57.009
"I'm
just a helpless woman

42:57.052 --> 42:59.620
"with no self-worth because
society says I'm nothing

42:59.664 --> 43:01.404
"unless a man saves me.

43:01.448 --> 43:03.102
"Save me, save me!

43:03.145 --> 43:05.974
"Your breath smells like
farts, but save me."

43:06.018 --> 43:08.586
"These mouth farts are
just for you, my dear.

43:08.629 --> 43:10.326
"My mother never ever loved me,

43:10.370 --> 43:12.241
"but you look just like
her so I'll take it."

43:15.854 --> 43:17.595
-Trigger.
-What?

43:17.638 --> 43:18.465
Trigger.

43:22.121 --> 43:23.339
Trigger.

43:24.689 --> 43:26.255
Trigger.

43:36.657 --> 43:38.224
You like this show?

43:38.267 --> 43:40.008
Love yourself.

43:40.052 --> 43:42.010
-Happy-Happy loves you.
-I'm sorry.

43:42.054 --> 43:43.098
You didn't say trigger.

43:44.230 --> 43:45.231
That was Ben.

43:46.362 --> 43:47.625
Who's Ben?

43:47.668 --> 43:49.801
My boyfriend. My ex-boyfriend.

43:51.237 --> 43:52.455
The hedgehog?

43:52.499 --> 43:53.413
Yeah.

43:54.806 --> 43:57.591
Your ex-boyfriend
is a fuzzy hedgehog?

43:59.158 --> 44:00.594
You got dumped by a hedgehog?

44:07.122 --> 44:10.517
Joy, come on. It's okay.

44:10.560 --> 44:12.084
No, it isn't.

44:12.127 --> 44:14.303
He's clearly a loser. You
could do better than that.

44:22.660 --> 44:24.662
It's okay. It's okay.

44:26.881 --> 44:30.058
Come on, stop being a
baby and just get over it.

44:30.102 --> 44:32.844
I can't just get over it.

44:32.887 --> 44:36.064
I wouldn't need to be here
if I could just get over it.

44:36.108 --> 44:38.066
Yeah, you can.

44:38.110 --> 44:39.720
Maybe if you weren't
so self-centered,

44:39.764 --> 44:42.288
you'd realize the world
has much bigger problems.

44:42.331 --> 44:44.725
So just let go and
move on already.

44:44.769 --> 44:46.074
I'm sure he has.

44:47.859 --> 44:49.512
You're an asshole.

44:54.692 --> 44:58.565
I am strong.

44:58.608 --> 45:00.567
I am smart.

45:01.524 --> 45:03.744
I am beautiful.

45:03.788 --> 45:07.661
I am enough for this moment.

45:07.705 --> 45:11.839
"I am Happy-Happy, and
I'm a fucking douchebag."

45:11.883 --> 45:14.712
I am a good person.

45:17.976 --> 45:19.673
I am a pizza.

45:30.597 --> 45:31.903
Joy?

45:35.950 --> 45:37.604
You know, I can see you.

45:38.997 --> 45:40.781
Joy, do you want a
popsicle that's made

45:40.825 --> 45:42.217
of American flag colors?

45:42.870 --> 45:43.915
I can't.

45:44.654 --> 45:45.525
Oh.

45:45.568 --> 45:46.308
I'm busy.

45:48.180 --> 45:49.311
Yeah, okay.

45:55.100 --> 45:55.927
Thanks!

47:14.266 --> 47:15.963
Okay, let's get you out, Nana.

48:19.592 --> 48:22.769
Today is August 19, 1998.

48:23.639 --> 48:26.686
It's 1:33 a.m.

48:47.272 --> 48:48.969
I'm so sorry.

48:49.013 --> 48:50.536
What are you doing?

48:52.494 --> 48:54.583
-No one's heard these.
-Don't!

48:54.627 --> 48:55.715
-They're gonna be buried with me.
-Don't do that!

49:07.335 --> 49:08.597
So what do you think?

49:10.077 --> 49:10.991
About what?

49:12.036 --> 49:13.298
The song.

49:15.039 --> 49:16.605
I thought it was beautiful.

49:19.347 --> 49:20.653
Do you want to see something?

50:37.251 --> 50:39.123
-Hey.
-Hey.

50:39.166 --> 50:41.386
It's so cool you're keeping
up with the painting.

50:41.429 --> 50:44.128
Oh, yeah, just messing around.

50:44.171 --> 50:46.043
I was just dropping
off my nana's meds,

50:46.086 --> 50:49.437
so I thought I'd check
in and see you're doing.

50:49.481 --> 50:50.395
How you doing?

50:50.438 --> 50:51.439
I'm good.

50:51.483 --> 50:53.006
No contact with Ben, right?

50:53.050 --> 50:54.312
None.

50:54.355 --> 50:56.401
No acting out at all?

50:56.444 --> 50:57.619
Nope. Totally clean.

51:01.493 --> 51:03.103
I guess I'll go see my nana.

51:03.147 --> 51:04.844
And Jim.

51:04.887 --> 51:07.238
Jim and I are taking a break
from each other right now.

51:07.281 --> 51:09.457
My sponsor suggested it.

51:10.284 --> 51:11.981
I am proud of you.

51:12.025 --> 51:14.201
Thanks.

51:18.510 --> 51:21.861
"Rough winds do shake
the darling buds of May,

51:21.904 --> 51:25.995
"And summer's lease hath
all too short a date.

51:26.039 --> 51:29.260
"Sometime too hot the
eye of heaven shines."

51:29.303 --> 51:30.609
I need to talk to Nana.

51:43.100 --> 51:44.753
Hi, Nana.

51:46.973 --> 51:49.715
Hey.

51:49.758 --> 51:51.543
Hi. It's Maddie.

51:52.152 --> 51:53.980
Hi.

52:01.944 --> 52:04.033
We could also
just be J and J,

52:04.077 --> 52:06.906
and "All The Way" could be
the name of our first album.

52:06.949 --> 52:09.561
Oh... I don't know.

52:09.604 --> 52:13.521
I haven't really thought
about us as an actual band.

52:13.565 --> 52:16.220
Kind of pursuing my
solo thing, you know?

52:16.263 --> 52:18.787
Thanks, though. You're
a really good artist.

52:23.227 --> 52:27.318
Let's start with "Here's
to the Trigger," yeah?

52:27.361 --> 52:31.365
All right. One, two, one, two...

52:31.409 --> 52:33.193
All right, what's wrong?

52:34.934 --> 52:36.196
Come on, Joy, what?

54:47.588 --> 54:49.851
So why do we need
to know about this?

54:50.983 --> 54:52.811
Mom, I told you.

54:52.854 --> 54:55.248
I just want you
to know who I am.

54:55.292 --> 54:57.294
I want you in my life.

54:57.337 --> 55:00.688
I've been working really
hard on being really honest

55:00.732 --> 55:02.821
and looking at my patterns

55:02.864 --> 55:06.520
and talking to people about it.

55:06.564 --> 55:08.130
I'm not the only one.
There are other people

55:08.174 --> 55:10.568
out there just like me
with the same addictions.

55:10.611 --> 55:12.004
We all just want love

55:12.047 --> 55:15.312
and intimacy and
connection, but...

55:15.355 --> 55:18.315
We don't know how to get it
without hurting ourselves.

55:19.620 --> 55:22.362
No one showed us how.

55:22.406 --> 55:24.495
It's okay.

55:24.538 --> 55:26.888
I'll make you spaghetti.
Your favorite.

55:31.545 --> 55:33.547
Your Uncle Louie was an addict.

55:35.854 --> 55:38.117
Couldn't stop buying hats.

56:25.164 --> 56:28.167
I enjoy reading books, writing,

56:28.210 --> 56:29.995
and playing the piano.

56:30.038 --> 56:32.780
But most of all, I love dancing.

56:37.872 --> 56:39.396
It was so crazy.

56:39.439 --> 56:43.487
I could really see my
parents, you know what I mean?

56:45.445 --> 56:48.274
They'll never be what
I want them to be.

56:48.317 --> 56:51.408
I can stop expecting
them to be somebody else.

56:51.451 --> 56:53.322
They're human beings

56:53.366 --> 56:55.673
who have no idea what
they're doing, just like me.

56:58.197 --> 57:00.025
One, two...

57:00.068 --> 57:01.592
I feel really stupid right now,

57:01.635 --> 57:03.463
like you're not getting it.

57:03.507 --> 57:05.465
I get it, Joy.
I just want to play.

57:05.509 --> 57:08.381
Do you get it? I don't
think you get it.

57:08.425 --> 57:09.556
I get it.

57:09.600 --> 57:11.471
-Do you though?
-I get it.

57:11.515 --> 57:13.430
Do you even realize how
long you've been talking?

57:13.473 --> 57:15.432
Oh. Okay.

57:15.475 --> 57:17.303
Let's play now.

57:20.219 --> 57:23.440
Are you acting out?
Is this acting out?

57:27.835 --> 57:28.923
Stop.

57:29.968 --> 57:32.840
I get it, Joy! I get it!

57:33.972 --> 57:36.583
My dad was drunk and left us.

57:36.627 --> 57:39.064
My mom was miserable
and left us.

57:39.107 --> 57:41.980
My sister won't talk to me.
I miss her.

57:44.112 --> 57:46.071
I'm wearing my
underwear inside out

57:46.114 --> 57:48.029
because I don't care enough
about myself to do laundry,

57:48.073 --> 57:50.292
so, yeah... I get it.

57:52.686 --> 57:54.514
This morning, I woke up thinking

57:54.558 --> 57:56.777
I was holding someone's hand...

57:57.865 --> 57:59.737
But it was just my other hand.

58:03.218 --> 58:05.482
Sometimes I sleep with a
phone book on top of me

58:05.525 --> 58:06.961
because it feels like love.

58:09.398 --> 58:11.096
I can't eat Gummy Bears

58:11.139 --> 58:12.880
because I think
they have feelings.

58:23.282 --> 58:24.152
You're my friend.

58:30.245 --> 58:32.030
Are you asking me or
are you telling me?

58:34.728 --> 58:36.948
You're my friend, Jim.

58:37.949 --> 58:39.037
I'm just saying.

58:42.954 --> 58:43.998
Yeah.

58:46.697 --> 58:48.263
You're my friend.

58:51.353 --> 58:52.093
Weirdo.

58:56.794 --> 58:58.578
You ready to play now?

58:59.710 --> 59:00.754
Yeah.

59:07.587 --> 59:09.067
I wrote a song.

01:01:04.573 --> 01:01:06.880
What the fuck is this?

01:01:06.924 --> 01:01:10.014
Maddie, we're just friends.

01:01:10.057 --> 01:01:13.539
I'm so stupid.

